{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17565996","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17565996"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:35:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:35:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18698"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18698","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18698"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.6,0.05,0.2,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11430"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106297"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11430"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18698"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88765"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"688"},{"type":"tags","id":"1307"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"3539"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26472"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35483"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35485"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36588"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44997"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106297","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106297"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a four-month history of fatigue, weight gain, cold intolerance, and dry eyes. She migrated from a mountainous region of Nepal eight months ago. She has no significant medical history apart from giving birth to her first child 12 months ago. She does not take any regular medications. She reports eating a vegetarian diet.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with pulse rate 58/min, blood pressure 110/70 mmHg, respiratory rate 14/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.5\u00b0C. She has dry skin and a small, firm, non-tender goitre. The remainder of the examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThyroid stimulating hormone: 12.4 mU/L (0.4-4.0)\u003Cbr/\u003EFree thyroxine: 8 pmol/L (10-20)\u003Cbr/\u003EFree triiodothyronine: 2.8 pmol/L (3.5-6.5)\u003Cbr/\u003EThyroid peroxidase antibodies: 15 IU/mL (\u003C35)\u003Cbr/\u003EThyroglobulin antibodies: 25 IU/mL (\u003C40)\u003Cbr/\u003EThyroid stimulating immunoglobulin: 1.4 IU/L (\u003C1.8)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her hypothyroidism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis","Iodine deficiency","Subacute thyroiditis","Postpartum thyroiditis","Graves\u0027 disease"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with clinical and biochemical features of primary hypothyroidism, characterised by elevated thyroid stimulating hormone and low free thyroid hormones. The key to determining the underlying cause lies in her background and antibody profile.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIodine deficiency\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely cause given her recent migration from mountainous Nepal, where iodine deficiency is endemic due to mountainous geography and limited access to iodised salt. The presence of a goitre and negative thyroid antibodies strongly support this diagnosis. Her vegetarian diet may also contribute to reduced iodine intake.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with significantly elevated thyroid peroxidase antibodies (usually \u003E1000 IU/mL). This patient\u0027s negative thyroid antibodies make autoimmune thyroiditis very unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPostpartum thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E occurs within the first year after pregnancy, and while this patient did give birth 12 months ago, the timing and pattern are not typical. Postpartum thyroiditis usually begins within one to four months postpartum with a hyperthyroid phase followed by hypothyroidism, and often resolves by 12 months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubacute thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E usually presents with thyroid pain and tenderness, often following a viral illness. The thyroid dysfunction typically begins with hyperthyroidism before progressing to hypothyroidism, and the thyroid is usually tender on examination.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGraves\u0027 disease\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes hyperthyroidism, not hypothyroidism. The patient\u0027s bradycardia and other symptoms are consistent with hypothyroidism. The dry eyes are more likely a non-specific finding rather than thyroid eye disease associated with Graves\u0027 disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Iodine deficiency remains a common cause of hypothyroidism in regions with limited access to iodised salt.","Normal or negative thyroid antibodies help distinguish iodine deficiency from autoimmune thyroiditis.","Recent migrants from regions with endemic iodine deficiency should be assessed for thyroid dysfunction."],"references":["Royal Australian College of General Practitioners. Hypothyroidism. Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/getattachment/8f4fe235-0ae2-48c1-951a-6358c54e4469/Hypothyroidism.aspx","Venn BJ, Mann JI. Effects of a vegetarian diet on the development of thyroid disorders. Nutr Rev. 2016;74(5):343-357. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11556367","Disorders that cause hypothyroidism. UpToDate. Available at: https://www.uptodate.com/contents/disorders-that-cause-hypothyroidism","Hypothyroidism. American Thyroid Association. Available at: https://www.thyroid.org/hypothyroidism/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88765"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18698"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88765"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-17T18:56:19+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-17T18:58:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11430"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106297"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"38","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/38"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf0f","name":"Public Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGro